        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How many hashtags should I use on social media posts? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The optimal number varies by platform for a balanced strategy:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Instagram:</strong> You can use up to 30, but 8-15 highly relevant hashtags is often most effective.</li>
              <li><strong>Twitter / X:</strong> 1-3 hashtags is recommended due to character limits.</li>
              <li><strong>Facebook:</strong> 3-5 hashtags is generally sufficient.</li>
              <li><strong>TikTok:</strong> 3-5 popular and niche hashtags can help with discoverability.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Focus on <strong>relevance and quality</strong> over quantity. Our AI tool helps you find the right balance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What makes a hashtag effective? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Effective hashtags are:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Relevant:</strong> Directly related to your content and audience.</li>
              <li><strong>Specific:</strong> Mix popular, broad hashtags with more niche ones to reach targeted users.</li>
              <li><strong>Readable:</strong> Use clear phrasing (e.g., <code>#SocialMediaTips</code> not <code>#socialmediatips</code>).</li>
              <li><strong>Current:</strong> Leverage trending topics when appropriate.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Our tools are designed to help you create hashtags that meet these criteria.</p>
          </div>
